I think there is confusion. 
In the experimental EARL server we set up at W3C the annotations do not have a type of a:Annotation (where a is the common annotea namespace) at all - they are merely EARL data. 
I suspect that it would have been more useful to make these annotations perhaps with a type that was different to the existing list (something like the Dublin Core relation element?). 
